@node "Intro" "Introduction"
                               Introduction

  RECENT is a mouse driven graphic interface for parsing AmiNet RECENT
 files. Interactivly select files to "get" from AmiNet. The result is
 a unix-able script to "cd" around AmiNet and "mget" the files as well
 as its .readme file.

  The reason for getting the .readme files; The SHORT description in the
 AmiNet RECENT file is truncated to 40 characters, and it seems most
 uploaders use longer SHORT descriptions.

  If you have and use the AmiNote program (written by me) it will look for
 the existence of the .readme file and pull the untruncated SHORT
 description from it. Then add it to the archive file as an AmigaDOS
 "filenote". Then optionaly Copy or Move the files to a bbs file directory
 or AmiNet Mirror.

  RECENT is written in ARexx, then crunched using The ReXXmAsHeR v0.4g.
@endnode

@node "Install" "Install / Setup"
Install / Setup

 1. Copy RECENT wherever you want.

 2. Copy the library file included in this archive libs/ directory to your
    LIBS: assigned directory.

    libs/apig.library        (v3.3 included in archive)

    2a. You must also have the following libraries in your LIBS: assigned
        directory;
 
        asl.library              (supplied with WB2+)
        rexxsyslib.library       (supplied with WB2+)
        rexxsupport.library      (supplied with WB2+)

 You must have RexxMast already running before you run RECENT. You can
 either drop RexxMast in your WBStartup drawer, or add it to your
 user-startup.

 RECENT requires Amiga OS 2.0+.
 It has been tested and found to work on my Amiga 2000 with OS 2.05 and 3.1.

                          @{" Install RECENT Now " rx "Install_RECENT.rexx"}  
@endnode

@node "Use" "Program Use"

 RECENT is started from a CLI or Shell. There are no command line args.
 Or by double-clicking the "Run_RECENT" icon.

                             @{"    Menus       " link "Menus"}
                             @{" User Interface " link "Interface"}

@endnode

@node "Menus" "Menus"

  Project
    @{" About " link "About"}
    @{" Quit " link "Quit"}

 Preferences
   Aminet Path
     @{"  Full Path     " link "Full_Path"}
