@node "About" "About"
  Displays program completion date, author name address and email phone
  number.

  The keyboard shortcut is Right-Amiga-A.
@endnode
@node "Quit" "Quit"
 Close any open files and exit program.

  The keyboard shortcut is Right-Amiga-Q.   (or click the Close gadget)
@endnode

@node "Full_Path" "Aminet Path - Full Path"
 Create output with full Aminet path to each file.
@endnode

@node "aminet_recent" "Aminet Path - aminet/recent/"
 Create output that will get all files from the /pub/aminet/recent/
 directory.

 These files are not "realy" in this directory, but Aminet makes "links"
 to the full path of all files listed in the RECENT file.

 Since you are not "cd"ing around Aminet, it should slightly shorten your
 overalll download time.
@endnode

@node ".readme" ".readme toggle"
 If you want to get the .readme files turn this menu option ON, indicated
 by a check mark next to it.

 If you do not want to get the .readme files turn this menu option OFF.

 You can turn this option on or off at any time, even in the middle of
 processing a RECENT file.

  The keyboard shortcut is Right-Amiga-R.
@endnode
@node "Save_Prefs" "Save Preferences"
 Selecting this menu option will save the current settings, including
 user interface options AmiNet RECENT path/filename, output file path
 and base-name, and .readme menu toggle state. And the RECENT program
 window position on your Workbench screen.

 These will be saved to files named "ENV:DFD/RECENT.prefs" and
 "ENVARC:DFD/RECENT.prefs".

  The keyboard shortcut is Right-Amiga-S.
@endnode
@node "Interface" "User Interface"

 RECENT @{"   " link "RECENT"} RAM:RECENT
 OUTPUT @{"   " link "OUTPUT"} RAM:AmiNet_18May         @{" ? " link "Info"} @{"  Do It!  " link "Do_It"}     @{"  Yes  " link "Yes"}@{"   No  " link "No"} @{" < " link "Back1"}
@endnode

@node "RECENT" "RECENT File"
 This is the path and filename of your AmiNet RECENT file. Click the gadget
 and a requester will pop up to choose the RECENT path and filename.

 The default is <current dir>RECENT
@endnode
@node "OUTPUT" "OUTPUT File"
 This is the path and base filename of the script file RECENT will
 generate. The "base" filename will be appended with an underscore and
 todays date. If your basename is "DH0:Work/Myfile" then the OUTPUT file
 will be "DH0:Work/Myfile_18May" (or whatever -todays- date is).

 The default is RAM:AmiNet_<date>
@endnode
@node "Info" "Information"
 Pops up a requester displaying how many files you have chosen and how
 many aproximate Kilobytes they add up to.
@endnode
@node "Yes" "Yes - I want this file."
 Clicking the "Yes" gadget tells RECENT that you want to "get" the file
 that is currently displayed on the top line.
@endnode
@node "No" "No - I don't want this file."
 Clicking the "No" gadget tells RECENT that you do not want to "get" the
 file that is currently displayed on the top line.

 After clicking "No", you have one chance to @{" Go Back 1 " link "Back1"} to it.
@endnode
@node "Do_It" "Do It!"
 When you click this gadget RECENT will go into action and start
 processing the AmiNet RECENT file.

 While processing this gadget reads "Abort". Clicking this gadget will
 close all open files and stop. You can do a "Quick Abort" by clicking
 the window Close gadget.
@endnode
@node "Back1" " < Go back 1"
 Clicking this gadget will take you back one file listing. This only works
 on listings you said "No" to.
@endnode

@node "History" "RECENT History"
 RECENT:
 v1.4 - 17-Jan-96
        Added "aminet/recent/" directory support.
        Fixed bug that would lock program if input RECENT file did not
         exist.

 v1.3 - 15-Dec-95
        Cleaned up the code some more. (a byte saved is a byte earned)
        Now lets you know if it can't save the preference file(s).
        Tried to address a problem that the "one person" I know of that
         uses this program reported; he said it choked on a "0K" file
         entry. I tried and tried to get it to "not work" for me, but
         couldn't... so didn't change anything.
        The biggest reason I am releasing this version is because v1.2
         never made it to AmiNet - as MOST my uploads don't! I think
         they must have a realy big "bit bucket" they send most uploads
         to.
        Updated the install script to check if your apig.library is older
         than the one supplied in this archive - if so, then copy the new
         one to your LIBS: directory.

 v1.2 - 03-Aug-95
        Fixed a bug that would exit program if you clicked "Yes" on a
         blank line.
        Fixed file requesters so they remember their paths. I thought they
         were before, but I guess not.
        Cleaned up the code a little more for size and speed.
        Added gadget to "Go back 1" file listing.
        Added "Info" gadget and requester.
        Added get ".readme" menu toggle.
        Added "Continue" when re-loading a previously Aborted RECENT file.
        Now will "Append" to output file if it already exists instead of
         overwriting it.
        Changed preferences files from "ENV:" to "ENV:DFD/" and now also to
         "ENVARC:DFD/".  ALL my programs now save to these DFD paths.

 v1.1 - 18-May-95
        Cleaned up some of the code to make it smaller and faster.
        Crunched it with The ReXXmAsHeR.

 v1.0 - 25-Apr-95
        First public release. Actually only a few friends got this one. It
        was compiled with RexxPlus and was so BLOATED it was embarassing.
        I didn't want to distribute it that way.
        Added GUI. (I wrote a shell based version several years ago but
        never released it publicly.)
@endnode

